            "title": "Natural gas shortages drive resurgence in nuclear power, as Asian nations reconsider following Fukushima; accelerating industry shift.",
            "id": "b4628f28-c16f-443a-9a3a-36591e0e1924",
            "description": "Recent disruptions in natural gas supplies have prompted countries across Asia and other regions to reconsider their aversion to nuclear power following the 2011 Fukushima incident. This change in attitude is reflected in the rising number of countries considering investments in nuclear energy as a more reliable and stable alternative.",
